  "instructions": [
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine teff flour, yeast, and warm water to activate the yeast.",
    "Let the mixture sit for 10 minutes to allow the yeast to ferment.",
    "Add rose water, garlic, onion, red bell pepper, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper to the bowl.",
    "Mix the ingredients thoroughly to combine.",
    "Knead the dough for 10 minutes to develop the gluten.",
    "Place the dough in a greased bowl, cover it with a damp cloth, and let it rise in a warm place for 1 hour.",
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Punch down the dough and shape it into a circle or rectangle, depending on your preference.",
    "Place the dough on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 15 minutes.",
    "Remove the bread from the oven and let it cool for 5 minutes.",
    "To assemble the wrap, place a few spoonfuls of your favorite Ethiopian stew or salad on the bread, and fold it in half."
